# UI & Styling Documentation Auto-Reference

When building UI components, **ALWAYS reference the appropriate indexed documentation** using @ mentions:

## React Development
- Use **@React Dev** for:
  - React 18+ features (Suspense, Transitions)
  - Hooks patterns (useState, useEffect, custom hooks)
  - Component composition
  - Context API
  - Performance optimization (memo, useMemo, useCallback)
  - Error boundaries

## Component Library (Radix UI)
- Use **@Radix-UI** when:
  - Building accessible components
  - Implementing dialogs, dropdowns, popovers
  - Working with form elements
  - Setting up keyboard navigation
  - Ensuring WCAG compliance
  - Using unstyled primitives

## Styling (Tailwind CSS)
- Use **@Tailwind Css** when:
  - Applying utility classes
  - Customizing theme
  - Creating responsive designs
  - Using arbitrary values
  - Implementing dark mode
  - Optimizing for production

## Storybook (Component Development)
- Use **@storybook** when:
  - Creating component stories
  - Documenting component APIs
  - Testing component variations
  - Setting up addons
  - Implementing accessibility testing
  - Building design system

## Example Usage Pattern

```typescript
// When building accessible components:
// @Radix-UI for accessible primitives and ARIA patterns
// @Tailwind Css for styling implementation

// When optimizing React components:
// @React Dev for hooks and performance patterns

// When documenting components:
// @storybook for story structure and best practices
```

## UI Best Practices
- **ALWAYS ensure accessibility** (WCAG AA minimum)
- **Use semantic HTML** elements
- **Implement keyboard navigation**
- **Test with screen readers**
- **Provide focus indicators**
- **Use proper ARIA attributes**

## Reminder
**Check Radix UI docs** for accessible component patterns, and **Tailwind docs** for optimal styling approaches before building new components.
